      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro hemolysis measurements across five pump operating conditions. The relative hemolysis index RH remained below 1.0 for all nominal conditions, consistent with the acceptance criterion. Inherent biological variability in red blood cell fragility across donor samples was acknowledged by the assessment team and assessed qualitatively through expert elicitation; no structured uncertainty quantification node was linked to this result."
